METADATAEXTENSION.DESCRIPTION: Contains a history of changes to the mapping.
METADATAEXTENSION.NAME: Change History
METADATAEXTENSION.VALUE:
[24/01/2021 LK] Modify to revert Sydney Changes [18/09/2020 JL] Modify to add Sydney Logic for EdgeTheo
[15/04/2014 LK] Modify to add null value for GameType
[23/11/2010 Joan Zhang] added ETLJobDtlID
[20/6/2005 Kavitha Sathish-Kumar] In exp tfm, Exp_Derivation, fields Gaming Activity Code and Sub Game Code are sourced from exp tfm, Exp_FormatSource instead of lookup transformation, Shortcut_To_Lkp_M_Alternative_Gaming_Code.
17 Jun 2005 Stephen Tyler, DWS What 1. Changed length of ports IN_AltGamingActvyCde,IN_AltSubGameCde and IN_AltSubGameName from 1 char to 2,2,35 Why: 1. Previous length was incorrect
16 Jun 2005 Stephen Tyler, DWS What 1. Changed Shortcut_To_Lkp_M_Alternative_Gaming_Code to now match GamingActivityCode and SubGameCode with input values Why 1. Previously tried to match subgamename with gamingactivitycode
[15/6/2005 Kavitha Sathish-Kumar] In order to cater for field Edge Theoretical to be output as a 2 place decimal value instead of integer, the following changes were made:- In source definition, field length modified from number (18,2) to (18,4); In expression transformation, instead of conversion to integer, field is multiplied by 100 to output to 2 decimal places (18,2); In lookup transformation, field length modified from number (6,2) to (18,2); In target definitions, field lengths modified from numeric (6,2) to (18,2); In all other transformations within mapping, before multiplication, field length conforms to (18,4) and after multiplication, it conforms to (18,2).
[13/12/2004 Jonas Ryding] Added '?' as default value for EGM_Denom and EGM_Gamecode because of issues when using lookps with NULL's allowed in fields that are part of the lookup condition (in m_Product).
